{
  "text": "Samples were tested in unconfined compression as previously described [CITATION_1] . For all mechanical testing a biopsy punch was used to create 5 mm \u00d8 cylindrical construct. The young's modulus was assessed using stress tests where the samples were compressed with a ramp displacement of 1 mm/s until 10% strain. The compressive modulus was taken as the slope of the stress strain curve between 0%-10% strain. The equilibrium compressive modulus was determined from the equilibrium force following unconfined compression testing to 25% strain.",
